The paper introduces a framework for dynamic adversarial discovery of information using reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses fairness and privacy concerns, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
